{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yang Earth Rat also known as <!--please transliterate all the hiragana readings into romaji and provide the kanji--> Yang Earth Rat''' (жИКе≠Р, гБ§гБ°гБЃгБИгБ≠гАБгБЉгБ©гБЃгБ≠гБЪгБњгАБгБЉгБ©гБЃгБ≠гАБгБЉгБЧ) is one element of the {{ill|Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive|ja|Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}.

It is the 25th combination in the Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive, preceded by {{ill|Ding Hai|ja|дЄБдЇ•}} and followed by {{ill|Ki Chou|ja|еЈ±дЄС}}. In the {{ill|Yin-Yang Five Elements Theory|ja|йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥}}, the {{ill|Wu|ja|жИК|1=Tsuchinoe (жИК)}} of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|еНБеє≤}} represents yang earth, while the {{ill|Zi|ja|е≠Р}} of the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|еНБдЇМжФѓ}} represents yang water, and according to the principle of mutual overcoming ({{ill|S≈Нkoku|ja|зЫЄеЙЛ}}; earth overcomes water).

