It is the 25th combination in the Sexagenary Cycle Comprehensive, preceded by {{ill|Ding Hai|ja|дЄБдЇ•|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Ki Chou|ja|еЈ±дЄС|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Wu|ja|жИК|1=Tsuchinoe (жИК)|12=draft|12=draft}} of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|еНБеє≤|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang earth, while the {{ill|Zi|ja|е≠Р|12=draft|12=draft}} of the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|еНБдЇМжФѓ|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang water, and according to the principle of mutual overcoming ({{ill|S≈Нkoku|ja|зЫЄеЙЛ|12=draft|12=draft}}; earth overcomes water).

